Name: Infantry
Description: Standard Infantry| not particularly exciting.

Name: Assault Infantry
Description: Assault Infantry are good at attacking| but take more damage in combat.

Name: Mountaineers
Description: Specialist infantry that has less issues traversing mountains.

Name: Marines
Description: Specialist infantry that can move after unloading from landers.

Name: Paratroopers
Description: Specialist infantry that can move after unloading from transport copters/planes.

Name: Guerillas
Description: Light Infantry that excel at hiding| even outside of Fog of War.

Name: Anti-Tank Infantry
Description: Infantry that sacrifice anti-infantry firepower and mobility for anti-tank weapons.

Name: Mortar Team
Description: Infantry capable of providing short-range fire support. (Unsure if will use)

Name: MG Team
Description: Slow-moving infantry that excels at defense against enemy infantry. (Unsure if will use)

Name: Command Infantry
Description: Infantry with good vision| capable of providing a boost to nearby units. (Unsure if will use)

Name: Motorcycle Infantry
Description: Fast-moving recon infantry with deminished capturing potential.

Name: Scout Car
Description: An unarmoured recon vehicle. Good for scouting and harassing infantry.

Name: Armoured Car
Description: An armoured recon vehicle. Can deal with unarmoured vehicles and infantry with ease.

Name: Truck
Description: A standard truck| capable of moving infantry or towed guns around| or resupplying land units..

Name: Halftrack
Description: An armoured truck| capable of moving infantry or towed guns. Comes with a defensive machine-gun.

Name: APC
Description: A slow but heavily-armoured transport. Can carry infantry or supplies| not easy to kill without tanks.

Name: Train
Description: A fast-moving ground transport vehicle that can carry several units and transport them| but is locked to rails.

Name: Engineering Dozer
Description: Capable of repairing vehicles or building defenses.

Name: Light Tank
Description: Lightly-armed and armoured| but quite fast. Counters armoured cars and infantry.

Name: Medium Tank
Description: One step up from light tanks| and the backbone of your armoured force for most of the game.

Name: Heavy Tank
Description: A big investment for big firepower. Can deal with most armoured units.

Name: Superheavy Tank
Description: An excessive purchase. Unrivalled on land| but slow| expensive and with limited fuel and ammo.

Name: Anti-Tank Gun
Description: A towed gun that excels at taking on armoured threats. Vulnerable to infantry.

Name: Tank Destroyer
Description: An anti-tank gun on a light tank chassis. Can punch far above it's armour class| but squishy to concentrated fire.

Name: Infantry Gun
Description: A step up from mortars| Infantry Guns are still pretty cheap and easy to move even without trucks.

Name: Assault Gun
Description: A  Very Big Gun(tm) on an armoured chassis. Devastating against soft targets and even some armoured targets| but slow.

Name: Howitzer
Description: A towed artillery piece| has good range| but requires trucks to move around.

Name: Mobile Artillery
Description: A howitzer on a medium tank chassis. Has good mobility| but sacrifices some range.

Name: Heavy Artillery
Description: A very large tracked gun platform. Very slow| very expensive| and takes time to set up| but has amazing range.

Name: Rocket Artillery
Description: A rocket launcher on the back of a truck. Has good range| but struggles to move in rough terrain.

Name: Anti-Air Gun
Description: A towed anti-aircraft gun. Good at dealing with copters and light planes| but struggles against more expensive aircraft.

Name: Anti-Air Tank
Description: An anti-aircraft gun on a light tank chassis. Good for mobile anti-air fire.

Name: Missile Carrier
Description: A multirole missile platform on the back of a truck. Can fire at enemy planes and ships from afar.

Name: CIWS Tank
Description: An anti-aircraft tank armed with a rapid-firing chaingun that can intercept air units and missiles alike| but cannot target ground forces.

Name: Scout Copter
Description: A cheap| fast and lightly-armed scout helicpter for recon duties. Poor at combat. (No Map Sprite)

Name: Attack Helicopter
Description: A standard helicopter; good against light ground units and other helicopters.

Name: Helicopter Gunship
Description: A heavy helicopter. Slow but packs an amazing punch against land targets| but cannot attack other helicopters.

Name: Transport Helicopter
Description: An unarmed transport helicopter. Can resupply  land units.

Name: Prop. Fighter
Description: A cheap propellor-driven aircraft. Good for taking out helicopters and occasionally harassing land units.

Name: Fighter Jet
Description: Your standard anti-air fighter plane. Unrivalled in air-to-air combat.

Name: Tactical Bomber
Description: A ground-attack aircraft that has some self-defense capabilities against other planes. Generally beats Prop. Fighters| but is best used against land targets.

Name: Seaplane
Description: A mix between a Fighter and Tactical Bomber| with the ability to operate off of carriers. Has less fuel in return.

Name: Level Bomber
Description: A large but slow-moving bomber aircraft that can decimate land units.  Has no way to defend itself against air units.

Name: Transport Plane
Description: An unarmed transport aircraft that can carry multiple units at once| but only load and unload on (Temp) Airports

Name: Support Ship
Description: An unarmed and slow-moving ship capable of resupplying other ships and laying seamines.

Name: Frigate
Description: A cheap warship capable of capturing oil rigs and navigating shallow water. Ineffective against combat ships.

Name: Destroyer
Description: A submarine-hunting warship. Excels at taking on submarines and lower-tier warships.

Name: Light Cruiser
Description: An anti-air warship. Provides ranged anti-air support for sea units and can carry helicopters. About as effective against surface ships as Destroyers.

Name: Heavy Cruiser
Description: A heavy anti-ship warship. Has strong ranged anti-ship capabilities| and can move and fire| but is vulnerable to submarines and not great against land targets.

Name: Battleship
Description: The pinnacle of naval firepower. Carries long-range guns that are great against land and sea targets alike| but is slow and vulnerable to air and sea attack.

Name: Carrier
Description: A flat-topped ship that can carry| repair and resupply Seaplanes. Provides some ranged anti-air firepower| but no anti-ship firepower.

Name: Submarine
Description: A stealthy naval attacker. Can submerge to become invisible and protected against non-destroyer attacks. Devastating against large ships.

Name: Transport Ship
Description: An unarmed transport ship. Can carry several land units| but only load/unload on (temp) ports.

Name: Invasion Ship
Description: An unarmed transport ship. Can carry troops and unload them onto beaches for a naval invasion.

Description: A flat-topped ship that can carry| repair and resupply Seaplanes. Provides some ranged anti-air firepower| but no anti-ship firepower.
